[1] Viet Nam (Quang Nam)
Date: Mon 14 Jul 2008
Source: Thanh Nien News [edited]
<http://www.thanhniennews.com/healthy/?catid=8&newsid=40215>


The central province of Quang Nam is suffering a
dengue fever outbreak, with more than 250
afflicted patients being treated at a local
hospital, the health department of Que Son
District announced Sunday [13 Jul 2008].

Local authorities said sick individuals who
contracted the disease but haven't checked into a
hospital may number in the hundreds.

[Byline: Ho Trong]

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-MBDS
<promed-mbds@promedmail.org>

[More dengue fever outbreaks have been reported
in Viet Nam from Quang Nam province in the above
newswire. The previous dengue fever outbreaks
were reported from Ca Mau province, Tien Giang
province, Soc Trang province, Ho Chi Minh City,
and the Mekong Delta provinces of Dong Thap, Bac
Lieu, Kien Giang, and Ben Tre (see prior PRO/MBDS
posting Dengue - Viet Nam (07) 20080708.2075).

For maps of Viet Nam with provinces, see:
<http://www.lib.utexas.edu/maps/middle_east_and_asia/vietnam_admin01.jpg> and
<http://www.angelfire.com/co/hongnam/vnmap.html>.

